 "coaching": {
  "headline": "This is the template win: objective control 25 majors to 11, Fangtooth at 7:00 and Mini Prime at 13:00 both yours, towers 7-4. Win games look like THIS — macro, not just a carry going nuclear.",
  "team": "Compare this to your fragile wins: you took the Fangtooth (7:00) and Mini Prime (13:00), won majors 25-11 and towers 7-4, off the back of a favored jungle (Xeebs Khaimera) and support (Mr_Meat Riktor) plus Cuban's Sparrow (11/6/7). Two enemy healers (Zinx, Grux) and — say it with me — no anti-heal, but here the objective snowball was fast enough that it didn't bite. This is the repeatable identity: control neutrals, take Fangtooth early, convert to towers. Do this and you don't need a 29-kill carry game.",
  "whatShiftedIt": "Nothing to fix in the macro — this is the model. The only loose thread is the reflex anti-heal vs the two healers; make it automatic so the one game the snowball stalls, you're still covered.",
  "perPlayer": {
   "a412baf3-dd17-4f89-8ecf-9d0704f3a79e": "Khaimera jungle, 6/5/13 on your 65% comfort hero, and the lane was FAVORED — you controlled neutrals and the Fangtooth/Mini Prime calls went your way. This is what your jungle looks like when you're on-role and not overextending. More of this.",
   "a0c393cc-1437-4bdc-8168-64676ce2166c": "Sparrow carry, 11/6/7 — your role, your hero, steady damage that the objective leads turned into a win. Six deaths is a touch high but you were ahead. The on-hit core (Storm Breaker/Spectra) over your build is the only optimizer nit.",
   "7c8ab99c-31c5-4ea5-a6fa-e0d6417c3f1b": "Riktor support, 1/8/12, favored lane — good engage setups (12 assists) that fed the objective snowball. Eight deaths is high for a support; pick your pull windows. Anti-heal vs Zinx+Grux was the standing miss.",
   "10edbf65-457d-48d0-9151-9df5b4fcb40a": "Skylar offlane, 5/2/2, low-death on a 118-game comfort hero — clean, held your side while the objectives were taken. As shot-caller this is the game to template: you called the Fangtooth at 7 and the Prime at 13. Do that every game.",
   "16f28434-561f-4f23-9454-40321f4a1ef3": "Wraith mid, 4/3/6, 45% on the hero into a losing Gideon lane — you didn't lose it hard and the team's macro covered the unfavored matchup. Fine supporting game; anti-heal vs the two healers was the team miss."
